In [[digital geometry]], a '''cutting sequence''' is a [[sequence]] of symbols whose elements correspond to the individual grid lines crossed ("cut") as a [[curve]] crosses a [[square grid]].<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Monteil | first1 = T. | doi = 10.4204/EPTCS.63.21 | title = The complexity of tangent words | journal = Electronic Proceedings in Theoretical Computer Science | volume = 63 | pages = 152 | year = 2011 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref>

[[Sturmian word]]s are a special case of cutting sequences where the curves are [[straight line]]s of [[irrational number|irrational]] slope.<ref name=PF152>Pytheas Fogg (2002) p.152</ref>

